{"name":"Forewarning","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Foreseeing his foes&rsquo; intentions, the psyker taps into the Warp and, like dropping a small pebble into a pool, sends ripples to slightly shift the course of events. Without moving a muscle, the psyker saves his ally from certain injury and leaves his enemy baffled.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Foresee and prevent attack on allies","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Perception 50","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":0,"test":"Psyniscience"},"range":"3*PR","sustained":"Free Action","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>For the duration of this power, a number of allies within range equal to the psyker&rsquo;s psy rating, plus the psyker himself, gain a bonus to all Evasion tests equal to twice the psyker&rsquo;s psy rating. Allies affected by this power lose its benefits as soon as they move out of range.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/Forewarning.png","effects":[],"_id":"14AQ0EDRgErI8vIt"}
{"name":"Winding Fate","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>By touching a character or item, the psyker sees visions into that subject&rsquo;s future and past. Though ghostly and laced with tendrils of Warp-smoke, these images reveal not only what was, but what is yet to be.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"See targetâ€™s past  or future","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Perception 50","action":"Full","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Psyniscience"},"range":"Self","sustained":"No","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>The vision lasts for a number of seconds equal to the twice the psy rating, and can be from the subject&rsquo;s future or past a number of days equal to the psy rating. The higher the psy rating, the more the psyker can control what his flashes focus on (at the GM&rsquo;s discretion).</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WindingFate.png","effects":[],"_id":"7k3KkD5YoGyFp0GT"}
{"name":"Cleansing Flame","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>The psyker projects his purity in a great gout of holy flames. The azure fires burn hotter than any mundane flame, blazing with the righteousness of the Emperor. Heretics and Daemons cannot hope to stand against the purifying flame.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Target enemies withHoly damage","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Psy raging 4","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":0,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"5*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Attack, Concentration","effect":"","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"1d10+PR+WPB","penetration":"","special":"Flame, Sanctified, Spray, DMG+WPB"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"82HUggMd4LTPZWuw"}
{"name":"Incursion","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Not content with merely summoning Daemons forth into reality, the psyker bends his unnatural powers toward the cowing of these unholy entities. Channelling the stuff of the Warp from which they are made, the psyker binds Daemons to his will.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Gain bonus to Daemonic  Mastery tests","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Willpower 45","action":"Full","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"Self","sustained":"Free Action","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>As long as this power remains in effect, the psyker gains a bonus to his Daemonic Mastery tests (see page 59) of +10 x psy rating.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"8Gp4QmmgoV47qaX6"}
{"name":"Inferno","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Focussing his power, the psyker ignites the very atmosphere surrounding his target, placing his foe in the midst of a sudden and violent conflagration.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Attack the target at range with an explosion  of fire","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Psy rating 5","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"10*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Attack, Concentration","effect":"","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"2d10+3*PR","penetration":"0","special":"Blast (PR), Flame"}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/Inferno.png","effects":[],"_id":"98x3c3ZTLg4mXGIB"}
{"name":"Summon Vermin","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Reaching out with his mind, the psyker calls out to nearby minor creatures, who unknowingly heed his summons.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"call out for small creatures","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Fellowship 30","action":"Full","focusPower":{"difficulty":0,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"1km*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>A number of small animals&mdash;such as rats, snakes, and similar small creatures&mdash;up to the psyker&rsquo;s PR within range come to the psyker&rsquo;s current location as quickly as possible. The time until the creatures appear depends on their speed and proximity, and they are likely to arrive over the course of several rounds or minutes. Once the creatures arrive, they behave normally and are not compelled to obey the psyker.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"9Z9k78KB8S2vIMma"}
{"name":"Enfeeble","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>The psyker lashes at his target with tendrils of Warp energy. The vile power quickly strips the victim of vitality, draining its spirit with every caress.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Temporarily  weaken target","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Toughness 35","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":0,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"20*PR","sustained":"Half Action","subtype":"Attack, Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker nominates a single target in range and line of sight who opposes this power with a Toughness test. If the target fails to resist the power, it is Stunned for one round. In addition, as long as this power remains in effect, if the target rolls doubles on any test it makes, it suffers a number of levels of Fatigue equal to half the psyker&rsquo;s psy rating (rounded down). A single target can only be affected by one instance of the Enfeeble power at a time, with other usages on the same target having no further effect.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/Enfeeble.png","effects":[],"_id":"BQ7QJBobl0uQfV2J"}
{"name":"Dark Flame","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Drawing on his own corruption, the psyker projects a gout of dark Warp-fire. The unnatural flames burn with the fires of the psyker&rsquo;s own damnation, consuming the souls of his enemies as surely as their bodies.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Target enemies with corrupting fires","cost":0,"prerequisite":"10 Corruption points","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":0,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"5*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Attack, Concentration","effect":"","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"1d10+PR","penetration":"","special":"DMG+CB, Pen=CB"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"BRuwmkwhujYfghdB"}
{"name":"Deja Vu","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>The psyker reaches into his target&rsquo;s mind and momentarily scrambles synapses and memories, causing the target to relive his last few moments.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Target repeats the last action","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Willpower 35","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"5*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker selects a single target, who opposes the test with an Ordinary (+10) Willpower test. If the psyker succeeds, the target must repeat his last exploit, such as firing a gun at a target who is no longer there or diving for cover from a grenade that has already detonated. This repeated deed counts as the target&rsquo;s Action for the round. If the action would be obviously harmful to the target (but not to an ally), the target automatically wins the Opposed test (scoring 1 more degree of success than the psyker).</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"BxxWxVUkYcX5LaXn"}
{"name":"Haemorrhage","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Drawing on his mastery of the living body, the biomancer accelerates his victim&rsquo;s heart rate beyond the bounds of biological possibility. Betrayed by his own body, the target&rsquo;s blood boils over, flooding his brain and bursting his over-taxed veins. Those nearby have their own hearts caught in the unnatural rhythm, suffering the same fate.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Wound target  at range","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Psy rating 4","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"10*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Attack, Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker nominates a single target in range and line of sight who opposes this power with a Toughness test. If the target fails to resist the power, it suffers Energy damage equal to the psyker&rsquo;s psy rating, plus one additional damage per degree of failure on its Toughness test; this damage ignores Toughness bonus and Armour. If this damage successfully kills the target, the psyker may immediately recast this psychic power as a Free Action on any legal target within 5 metres of the original target.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/Haemorrhage.png","effects":[],"_id":"DHFXGHJCE8VDrh2l"}
{"name":"Invigourate","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>The psyker draws upon the energies of the Warp to galvanise the flesh, a possibly hazardous endeavour but one that can be essential to continue the warband&rsquo;s efforts. Newly empowered, the Acolytes can continue afresh.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Remove levels of Fatigue equal to psy rating","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Toughness 30","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":0,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"1","sustained":"No","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker can remove a number of levels of Fatigue from himself and allies within range. He can chose how many levels to reduce per character, but the sum of all levels removed from all characters cannot exceed his psy rating. This power is very taxing and requires at least 12 hours of recovery before it can be used again.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/Invigourate.png","effects":[],"_id":"DLs7qd7ZvbkzDxr5"}
{"name":"Impel","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Developing psykers often instinctively exhibit rudimentary versions of the abilities shown in the disciplines of the Scholastica Psykana. Whereas an accomplished telekine can manipulate objects with more deftness than he could with his actual hands, an untrained psyker might simply lash out, shoving objects with blunt, yet effective, mental force.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"a rough telekine push","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Willpower 30","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"5*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Attack, Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker chooses a target, which can be an object or character, and pushes it directly away from him a number of metres equal to his psy rating. To determine the maximum weight the psyker can push, consult the table on page 248 of the DARK HERESY Core Rulebook, substituting the psyker&rsquo;s PR and WPB for SB and TB. If the target is a character, he opposes the power with a Challenging (+0) Strength test. If the target fails with two or more degrees of failure, he is also knocked Prone. If the psyker wins by 3 or more degrees of success, the target sufers 1d5+PR damage and 1 level of Fatigue.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"EGBJwALV6EJN14ok"}
{"name":"Weapon Jinx","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>The psyker reaches out with his power, fouling the mechanisms of nearby weapons.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"fouling the mechanisms of nearby weapons.","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Intelligence 35","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"5*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker chooses a number of ranged weapons within range up to the psyker&rsquo;s psy rating, with each Best craftsmanship weapon counting as two weapons for the purposes of this power. Affected weapons count as Poor craftsmanship until repaired. If the psyker&rsquo;s degrees of success on the Focus Power test exceed the psy rating of the power, then the affected weapons also jam immediately. Should the psyker fail the test with 2 or more degrees of failure, his own ranged weapons jam immediately.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"G8EQMVoXW2vNAkPc"}
{"name":"Sanctuary","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>The psyker summons a barrier of holy force, pushing back the Daemon and deflecting the blows of heretics</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Allies gain force field protection","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Willpower 45","action":"Full","focusPower":{"difficulty":0,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"Self","sustained":"Half Action","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker selects a number of allies up to psy rating (which may include the psyker) within 10 metres x psy rating. For the duration of the power, each affected character benefits from a force field with a protection rating of 5 x PR and no overload chance. In addition, Daemons must pass a Challenging (+0) Willpower test in order to move toward an affected character.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"GqwaxmLCnWWuDBYx"}
{"name":"Possession","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>For most psykers, the possibility of a Daemon of the Warp possessing their body is their greatest fear, a fear that they must contend with each time they use their unnatural powers. For some, however, it is merely another path to power. Confident in his own strength of will, the psyker allows a minor Warp beast to temporarily enter his flesh, imbuing him with unholy resilience and strength.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Gain daemonic powers","cost":0,"prerequisite":"20 Corruption points","action":"Full","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"Self","sustained":"Free Action","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>While the power is sustained, the psyker gains the Daemonic (X) and Unnatural Strength (X) traits, where X equals half his psy rating, as well as the Deadly Natural Weapons trait. In addition, the psyker must succeed at a Challenging (+0) Willpower test each round the power is sustained or enter a Frenzied state per the Frenzy talent (see page 127 of the Dark Heresy Core Rulebook). While Frenzied, the psyker must continue to sustain the power (in a special exception to the prohibition on using psychic powers while Frenzied). <br />Psychic Phenomena: A result of Psychic Phenomena when using this power means that a more powerful Daemon, as chosen by the GM, has taken the psyker&rsquo;s invitation. The psyker must succeed in an Opposed Willpower test against the Daemon or become possessed (see page 69).</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"IaMzMzz7m3Xyxqme"}
{"name":"Suggestion","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Although a far cry from the mind-inluencing techniques of a trained telepath, many wyrds and nascent psykers possess a preternatural ability to convince others of small falsehoods. As with many of the powers such psykers evince, this is a useful survival mechanism, allowing the psyker to evade detection.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"convince others of small falsehoods","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Rank 1 (Known) in the Deceive skill","action":"Full","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"1*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker convinces the target of a small, but potentially important lie. The target opposes this with a Challenging (+0) Willpower test, which the GM should modify based on the credibility and scope of the lie. In the case of clearly impossible lies, the target succeeds automatically (scoring 1 more degree of success than the psyker). For instance, a human psyker might suggest that a guard has already checked his identification, but would have no possibility of convincing that same guard that the psyker is a Space Marine.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"K50815oLnoIk1OXI"}
{"name":"Foreboding","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>The psyker gains an unnatural sixth sense. With this inexplicable insight, he knows how and where his enemies will attack, dodging blows and lasblasts with contemptuous and frightening ease.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Foresee and prevent incoming attacks","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Psyniscience rank 1","action":"Reaction","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Perception"},"range":"Self","sustained":"No","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>In any situation where the psyker would be called upon to make an Evasion test, he may instead attempt to use this power. If the power is successful, the psyker avoids the attack exactly as if he has passed an Evasion test with the number of degrees of success he scored on the Focus Power test.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/Foreboding.png","effects":[],"_id":"Lsfufk5po6XimO6E"}
{"name":"Luck","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Many undiscovered psykers are known for their luck or good fortune. Such psykers might not even be aware of their own true nature, but subconsciously manipulate events through a variety of psychic effects, from telepathic hints to telekinetic nudges. Of course, if others knew the true reason for their ability to seemingly defy the odds, they would not consider these psykers fortunate, but damned&mdash;as might a psyker himself.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"gain a bonus to next action","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Perception 30","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":0,"test":"Awareness"},"range":"Self","sustained":"No","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>If the Focus Power test is successful, the psyker gains a bonus of 5 plus his psy rating on the next test he attempts this round. If the psyker fails the Focus Power test by 2 or more degrees of failure, his misguided attempt to call on the Warp backires, and the resultant psychic ripples inlict a penalty equal to twice his psy rating on his next test this round.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"M5ZxtoFzwuLG9ReK"}
{"name":"Summoning","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Drawing on his Warp-born powers, the psyker weakens the veil twixt reality and the Immaterium, paving the way to summon forth its unholy denizens.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Gain bonus for summoning Daemon","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Willpower 35","action":"Full","focusPower":{"difficulty":0,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"Self","sustained":"Free Action","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>As long as this power is sustained, the psyker gains a bonus of +10 x psy rating to Forbidden Lore (Daemonology) tests made to summon Daemons.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"NnrlybKCDNzItJ4B"}
{"name":"Fire Shield","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>With but a gesture, the psyker summons a wall of shimmering, unnatural fire in the air before him. Any who would strike the pyromancer must contend with fiery retribution, as flames leap outward, travelling in reverse down the path of the bullet or lasbolt to strike the psyker&rsquo;s assailant.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Surround body in spectral flame","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Agiility 40","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":0,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"20*PR","sustained":"Free Action","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>While this power is in effect, any character in range and line of sight that successfully strikes the psyker with an attack immediately suffers Energy damage equal to the psyker&rsquo;s psy rating. The degrees of success on this attack are equal to those from the Focus Power test, and the inflicted damage is not reduced by Armour or Toughness bonus.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"PR","penetration":"0","special":"Flame"}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/FireShield.png","effects":[],"_id":"OC1ZgkVAk2dkvroG"}
{"name":"Warp Perception","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>The psyker opens his senses to the Warp, allowing unnatural tendrils of energy to augment his own perceptions. His flesh no longer limited, he casts his gaze wider and hungrily scents prey from farther afield.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Gain Unnatural Senses trait","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Willpower 35","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":0,"test":"Psyniscience"},"range":"Self","sustained":"Half Action","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker gains the Unnatural Senses (X) trait, where the X value is equal to the psy rating multiplied by 10.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WarpPerception.png","effects":[],"_id":"OHScpuBqOhOgJWzv"}
{"name":"Molten Beam","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>The pyrokine projects from his hands a blindingly bright beam of sun-hot energy. At the touch of this blazing ray, plasteel liquefies and flesh bursts into ash.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Attack target at range with a beam of energy","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Psy rating 4","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":0,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"5*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Attack","effect":"","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"1d10+5+3*PR","penetration":"2*PR","special":"Melta"}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/MoltenBeam.png","effects":[],"_id":"OpXqKsAwmp4yV9hU"}
{"name":"Misfortune","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Twisting fate, the psyker focuses his inner eye to ensure that his foe suffers every possible calamity that ill-fortune could provide. From embarrassing mishaps to life-and-death struggles, chance itself betrays the target at every turn.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Inflict bad luck  on target","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Willpower 45","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"20*PR","sustained":"Free Action","subtype":"Attack, Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker nominates a single target in range and line of sight who opposes this power with a Willpower test. If the target fails to resist the power, misfortune follows it wherever it goes. For the duration of this power, the target&rsquo;s Armour points are reduced in all locations by half the psyker&rsquo;s psy rating, rounded up. The target&rsquo;s weapons also jam on any attack in which they fail to hit their target.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/Misfortune.png","effects":[],"_id":"PODxNAJrUJviU6o6"}
{"name":"Precognition","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>In one of the most viscerally intense applications of the Divination discipline, the psyker witnesses solid and perfectly lifelike visions of his own future. Peering into moments yet to come, he can use this information to ensure or avoid future fates.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Gain re-rolls","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Perception 45, Willpower 45","action":"Full","focusPower":{"difficulty":-20,"test":"Psyniscience"},"range":"5*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker gains a number of re-rolls equal to his psy rating that last until the beginning of the his next turn. For the duration of that round, whenever the psyker or an ally in range makes a test or damage roll, the psyker may spend one of the rerolls to allow that ally to re-roll all dice involved in the roll. If the psyker is killed or rendered Unconscious before the beginning of his next turn, all remaining re-rolls are lost.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/Precognition.png","effects":[],"_id":"PyqWMl4J6hjWRc44"}
{"name":"Ignite","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>The psyker draws upon his anger, whether knowingly or not, and channels the Warp to produce a physical manifestation of his burning rage.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Illuminate roughly 5m","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Willpower 30","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":0,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"5m x PR","sustained":"Half","subtype":"Attack, Concentration","effect":"<p><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16.6667px;\">The psyker creates a small lame, </span></span><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16.6667px;\">approximately a centimetre across, at a point within </span></span><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16.6667px;\">range and line of sight. The lame is not large or hot </span></span><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16.6667px;\">enough to inlict damage, but can illuminate roughly </span></span><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16.6667px;\">a 5 metre radius. It can also ignite combustible </span></span><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16.6667px;\">materials at the GM&rsquo;s discretion, with the chance of </span></span><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16.6667px;\">igniting an object increasing the longer the psyker </span></span><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16.6667px;\">sustains the power. If the target of this power is a </span></span><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16.6667px;\">character, he must pass a Challenging (+0) Agility </span></span><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16.6667px;\">test each round the psyker sustains the power after </span></span><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16.6667px;\">the irst, or catch ire. The target gains a +30 bonus </span></span><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16.6667px;\">to this test on any round during which he performs </span></span><span style=\"font-family: sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16.6667px;\">an action with the Movement subtype.</span></span></p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/Ignite.png","effects":[],"_id":"SlsljkZeaOV8WK3n"}
{"name":"Smite","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Drawing on the electric field of his own body, the psyker projects crackling bolts of bio-lightning, transforming his very life force into destructive energy. Diviners often claim that one can tell much about the state of a biomancer&rsquo;s soul from the colour and appearance of this power.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Attack target with ranged bio-lightning","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Willpower 40","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":0,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"20*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Attack, Concentration","effect":"","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"1d10+PR","penetration":"4","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/Smite.png","effects":[],"_id":"TNAOUMd2129htVjl"}
{"name":"Prescience","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>The psyker sees brief, fuzzy flashes into his immediate future, which he can use to guide the warband&rsquo;s aim against their enemies. Though the glimpses are short, such foretelling can mean the difference between life and death when in combat.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Gain bonuses in  combat skills","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Psyniscience Rank 1","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":0,"test":"Psyniscience"},"range":"3*PR","sustained":"Half Action","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>For the duration of this power, the psyker and a number of allies equal to his psy rating within range, gain a bonus to their Weapon Skill and Ballistic Skill tests equal to twice the psyker&rsquo;s psy rating. Allies affected by this power lose its benefit as soon as they move out of range.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/Presience.png","effects":[],"_id":"TbxRCmlpBJbFSUdk"}
{"name":"Scrier's Gaze","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>The most accomplished diviners are not only able to see into the future, but also the present. Unbound by the limits of mere physical vision, his mind peers far and wide, with little able to hide from his sight.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"See events elsewhere","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Psyniscience rank 2","action":"Special","focusPower":{"difficulty":0,"test":""},"range":"Self","sustained":"No","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>To begin the ritual, the psyker must spend at least thirty minutes using assorted psychic foci to concentrate his vision&mdash; drawing Tarot cards, casting runes, gazing deep into fire, or other methods as varied as the stars of the Imperium. At the end of this time, he makes his Focus Power test to project his vision over the area, with the GM revealing information based on the degrees of success, as described on Table 6&ndash;4: Scrier&rsquo;s Gaze Results.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/ScriersGaze.png","effects":[],"_id":"UvBm1jgIjDJBxINl"}
{"name":"Life Leech","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>The psyker latches on to his target&rsquo;s life force and tears it from the hapless victim&rsquo;s body. The psyker absorbs this stolen essence, using it to reinvigourate and bolster his own flesh.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Drain targetâ€™s  vitality","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Toughness 40","action":"Full","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"10*PR","sustained":"Free Action","subtype":"Attack, Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker nominates a single target in range and line of sight who opposes this power with a Toughness test. If the target fails to resist the power, he suffers 1d10 + psy rating Toughness damage, and the psyker gains Unnatural Toughness (1) trait, with its value increased by 1 for every full 5 points of Toughness damage the power inflicts. This Unnatural Toughness trait remains for as long as the power&rsquo;s effect persists.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/LifeLeech.png","effects":[],"_id":"VZHa6y86OvSvUlke"}
{"name":"Shape Flesh","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Powerful biomancers are able to bend the living body to their will with great finesse. At the heights of ability, a psyker can mould flesh with an expertise any sculptor would envy.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Alter targetâ€™s appearance","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Perception 35, Toughness 30","action":"Full","focusPower":{"difficulty":10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"1","sustained":"Free Action","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker chooses himself or an organic target that he can physically touch. The target&rsquo;s physical appearance changes to a new form of the psyker&rsquo;s choosing for the duration of the power. The amount and precision of the alterations depend on the final psy rating used. Following are some broad guidelines, but GMs can further alter the range of the power as needed.</p>\n<p>&bull; PR 1&ndash;3: The psyker can alter subtle flesh shapes, tones, and colours to distort the appearance of the target. He does not have direct control over what the end result looks like.</p>\n<p>&bull; PR 4&ndash;6: The psyker can alter flesh, hair, eyes, and any other physical features. He can choose how the features will be altered, but does not have the precision to mimic others.</p>\n<p>&bull; PR 7&ndash;9: The psyker can change any physical feature of the target to resemble another individual. However, the psyker must have a pic record of the individual, or have seen him before.</p>\n<p>&bull; PR 10+: The psyker can shape his target to exactly mimic another individual. Additionally, he can use the power to morph the target into a form that no longer appears human. All tests to identify the target&rsquo;s true identity suffer a penalty equal to 5 x PR for the duration of the power. The effects of the power on a target other than the psyker remain in effect for the duration of the power, regardless of how far away from the psyker the target becomes.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/ShapeFlesh.png","effects":[],"_id":"XBYfI33UATjZ5zAX"}
{"name":"Fiery Form","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Unnatural flame engulfs the psyker&rsquo;s entire body. He is cloaked in sheets of fire that somehow do not harm him, but burns any nearby with horrifying results.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Summon a burning wall of fire","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Psy rating 4","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"Self","sustained":"Half Action","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>While this power is in effect, all of the psyker&rsquo;s melee attacks deal additional Energy damage equal to his psy rating and gain the Flame quality. In addition, at the end of each of the psyker&rsquo;s turns in which he sustains this power, he emits a Psychic Blast centred on his location. Each character within the area of the blast, with the exception of the psyker himself, are struck.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"1d10+PR","penetration":"0","special":"Blast (PR), Flame"}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/FieryForm.png","effects":[],"_id":"XFJTYgVUU6quW2Kz"}
{"name":"Infernal Gaze","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>The psyker opens his soul to the Warp, his eyes reflecting a dark vision of the Realm of Chaos. Those who witness this sight are seared to the very soul.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Infliect damage non-Daemon foes","cost":0,"prerequisite":"15 Corruption points, Willpower 45","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"5*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Attack, Concentration","effect":"<p>This power affects all characters within range and line of sight, friend and foe, who do not possess the Daemonic trait. Each affected character opposes the power with a Challenging (+0) Willpower test. Any character who fails suffers Energy damage equal to the user&rsquo;s psy rating plus Corruption bonus, ignoring armour and Toughness bonus, and gains Insanity points and Corruption points equal to half the user&rsquo;s psy rating.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"XyGeRg5d85StCblK"}
{"name":"Flame Breath","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Using his body as a conduit for his Warp-drawn power, the psyker expels a torrent of flame from his mouth and eyes. Even his allies can find the sight terrifying as his foes are burned with his unnatural exhalations.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Attack target at range with cone of flame","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Psy rating 3","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":0,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"20*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Attack","effect":"","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"1d10+2+2*PR","penetration":"0","special":"Flame"}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/FlameBreath.png","effects":[],"_id":"ZQrAP8av7eNt2yn5"}
{"name":"Hammerhand","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Imbuing his muscles with psychic force, the psyker brings down the wrath of the Emperor of Mankind in powerful strikes that shatter ceramite and plasteel.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Imbue self and allies with Unnatural Strength","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Psy rating 3","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"5*PR","sustained":"Free Action","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker selects a number of allies within range equal to his psy rating (which may include the psyker). While the power persists, the affected characters gain the Unnatural Strength (X) trait where X is equal to the user&rsquo;s psy rating, or increases their existing trait&rsquo;s value by 4. This benefit ends if a character moves out of range.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"aU2vUWRB8txtRECs"}
{"name":"Warp Speed","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Tapping into the power of the Empyrean, the psyker suffuses his body with energy, pushing himself beyond physical limits. While under the effects of this power, the psyker moves with unbelievable speed, ensuring that no heretic is swift enough to escape justice.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"ncrease own Agility and combat skills","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Psy rating 5","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"Self","sustained":"Free Action","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker gains the Unnatural Weapon Skill, Unnatural Ballistic Skill, and Unnatural Agility traits, all at values equal to his psy rating.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/WarpSpeed.png","effects":[],"_id":"ahqANMlEyFHuMaJ4"}
{"name":"Sunburst","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>The psyker releases a nova of fiery energy from his body. As the psyker focuses his power, a blazing aura coalesces around him, growing brighter and hotter before rapidly expanding outward in all directions. As the calm at the eye of the firestorm, the psyker is untouched, while all around him is reduced to ash and cinder.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Release a nova of fire","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Psy rating 4","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":0,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"20*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Attack","effect":"","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"1d10+2+2*PR","penetration":"0","special":"Flame"}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/Sunburst.png","effects":[],"_id":"gj2os6cwCIXfrAkH"}
{"name":"Cauterise","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>With careful application of his powers, the psyker applies intense heat to a wound on his own flesh or to the flesh of an ally, quenching the flow of blood. The effect is quite painful, but certainly preferable to bleeding to death. The use of this power generates a focused and intense heat that rivals advanced medicae equipment, and certainly far exceeds the effects of ordinary battlefield cauterisations.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Remove blood loss from target","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Willpower 45","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":20,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"1","sustained":"No","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker chooses himself or another character he can physically touch. If the target is suffering from Blood Loss, successfully using the power removes that condition.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/Cauterise.png","effects":[],"_id":"iDBs550bb9cEQPMp"}
{"name":"Word of the Emperor","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>The psyker speaks with the very voice of the Emperor, causing his enemies to cringe in pain and terror. Bolstering his denunciations and catechisms of hate with psychic resonance, the psyker ensures that heretics and Daemons must struggle past his holy words in order to lay hand or claw upon him.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Enemies suffer penalties to attack user","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Fellowship 30","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"10*PR","sustained":"Half Action","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>Whilst the power remains in effect, whenever a character within range takes an Attack action targeting the psyker, the attacker must pass a Challenging (+0) Willpower test or suffer a &ndash;5 penalty to his attack roll for each degree of failure.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"iSyzFvc6qmj6gVe0"}
{"name":"Ill Omen","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Drawing on Mankind&rsquo;s natural, and often quite justified, superstitious fears, the psyker bleeds just a miniscule drop of the Warp&rsquo;s inluence into the world. The result, while perhaps logically explainable, nonetheless instils a deep unease in those who witness it&mdash;an unmistakable sense of worse things to come. The exact nature of the omen could take any number of forms, including a raven crying three times, a small plant wilting, a disturbingly familiar patina of rust, animals spooking with no apparent cause, or anything else that might unnerve the target.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"give an omen to a target","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Rank 1 (Known) in the Psyniscience skill","action":"Full","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"10*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker chooses a single target within range and line of sight, who opposes this power with a Challenging (+0) Logic test. If the power is used during structured time and the target fails to resist, he sufers a &ndash;10 penalty to all tests for PR rounds. If used during narrative time, the psyker instead chooses a time within the next PR hours for the target to experience the omen. The GM determines the efects on the target&rsquo;s behaviour, but a likely result is that the target rethinks his current course of action or direction he is travelling. The GM should use the psyker&rsquo;s degrees of success and PR, as well as his suggestion for the form of the omen, in determining the outcome.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"jNGMyNzJMnMsfEAh"}
{"name":"Manipulate Flame","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Reaching out with his mind, the psyker grasps nearby flame and moulds it to his desire. The flames dance to his tune, moving to untouched areas or falling quiet at their master&rsquo;s command.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Extinguish or control fire","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Willpower 35","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":20,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"10*PR","sustained":"Half Action","subtype":"Attack","effect":"<p>The psyker chooses a patch of fire in range and line of sight with a radius no greater than PR metres. Each round, he can either extinguish or control the fire. If he extinguishes the fire, this power ends and the fire goes out. If he controls the fire, he can move it up to a number of metres equal to his psy rating per round along a flammable surface.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/ManipulateFlame.png","effects":[],"_id":"jdcGnBuHR53MqcGy"}
{"name":"Sacrifice","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>The psyker uses the flesh and blood of a willing or unwilling victim to fuel his dark powers. Whether ending a life or merely opening a vein, the sacrifice calls out to the Warp, drawing the attentions of Daemons and bolstering the psyker&rsquo;s malevolent abilities.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Gain bonuses to cast powers after wounding foes","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Willpower 45","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"Self","sustained":"No","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>This power can only be used if the psyker has inflicted damage on a target (possibly himself) since the beginning of the previous round. If the Focus Power test succeeds, the psyker gains a +5 bonus to his next Focus Power test for each point of damage inflicted (after reductions for armour and Toughness bonus) with the preceding attack. This bonus must be used within 1 hour.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"jlKK72lbNa2fbhoB"}
{"name":"Banishment","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Speaking words of banishment, the psyker draws on his faith and reaches out to sever the cords tying a Daemon to reality. Its hold in realspace broken, the Daemon is cast back into the depths of the Warp.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Hurl daemonic target back into the Warp","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Psy rating 3","action":"Full","focusPower":{"difficulty":-20,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"10*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Attack, Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker selects a target in range and line of sight, which must possess the Warp Instability trait. The targeted Daemon must immediately make a Willpower test, with a &ndash;5 penalty for each degree of success on the Focus Power test. The target suffers 1 point of Energy damage per degree of failure on the test, ignoring Toughness bonus and armour. If this would deal damage equal to or in excess of the target&rsquo;s remaining wounds, it is immediately cast back into the Warp.&nbsp;</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"k9i6gkAzNlZAKH5c"}
{"name":"Foretelling","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Focussing his preternatural senses onto another person or object, the psyker receives a brief glimpse of the future.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"receive a brief and unclear image of the future","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Perception 35","action":"Full","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Psyniscience"},"range":"5*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker chooses a single character or item within range and receives a brief and unclear image of the future, giving him a rough idea of one thing that will happen to the target within a number of minutes up to the psyker&rsquo;s PR. The GM decides what information the psyker receives, with additional degrees of success on the Focus Power test yielding more important information. For example, the psyker might learn that the character will be the target of an attack or will himself become violent, or that a cogitator will be accessed by an unknown individual. The psyker cannot select himself as the target of this power.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ktnoBwjlbebT6npt"}
{"name":"Cursed Earth","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>The psyker calls forth crackling tendrils of dark energy to imbue an area of ground with the power of the Warp. This area of cursed earth helps Daemons sustain their grip in reality, weakening the veil between realspace and the Warp. Those who step on the cursed ground feel revulsion and terror, recoiling from the unnatural presence.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Daemons and psykers gain benefits in region","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Willpower 40","action":"Full","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"1*PR","sustained":"Free Action","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker selects an area of ground with a radius in metres equal to psy rating. While the power is sustained, Daemons standing within this area increase the value of their Daemonic trait by half psy rating and receive a bonus of +5 x psy rating to Warp Instability tests. In addition, psychic powers used within the affected area add +10 to Focus Power tests and rolls on Table 6&ndash;2: Psychic Phenomena (see page 196 of the Dark Heresy Core Rulebook). Those in the presence of the Cursed Earth may experience disturbing Warp phenomena at the GM&rsquo;s discretion (see Table 3&ndash;2: Warp Phenomena on page 137).</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"mIr4r0gHyHBklaba"}
{"name":"Purge Soul","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Using the corruption in his target&rsquo;s soul as kindling, the psyker ignites an inner fire, burning away the target&rsquo;s tainted soul.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Target foe using Willpower","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Willpower 35","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"10*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Attack, Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker chooses a target within range and line of sight, who opposes the power with a Willpower test. If the psyker wins the Opposed test, the target suffers 1 point of Energy damage per degree of success on the test, plus an amount equal to the target&rsquo;s Corruption bonus, ignoring armour and Toughness bonus.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"noGhYbeuYnO3cgkH"}
{"name":"Aura of Fear","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Summoning his eldritch powers, the psyker projects a fearful aura. All those who witness him see their own deepest fears projected onto the psyker, not with their eyes, but in their minds.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"gains the Fear (1) trait","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Fellowship 35, 5+ Insanity points","action":"Full","focusPower":{"difficulty":-20,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"Self","sustained":"Half Action","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker gains the Fear (1) trait as long as he sustains this power.</p>\n<p>Psychic Phenomena: Instead of rolling for Psychic Phenomena should the situation call for it, the psyker instead must take a Fear (4) test and also suffer Warp Shock as per page 289 of the DARK HERESY Core Rulebook if he fails.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"nrNXVe3zmrgeEUKu"}
{"name":"Holocaust","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>The psyker ignites his very soul in a devastating conflagration that washes out from him in all directions. It is said that the flames of this power burn not only flesh, but the very souls of the psyker&rsquo;s enemies, destroying them utterly&mdash;and that the psyker risks consuming his own soul in the process.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Burn surrounding enemies withWarpfire","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Psy rating 5","action":"Full","focusPower":{"difficulty":-20,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"Self","sustained":"Full Action","subtype":"Attack, Concentration","effect":"<p>Each round the psyker sustains Holocaust, he emits a psychic blast centred on himself. He is not affected by the blast, but each turn the psyker sustains the power he suffers 1d10+psy rating Energy damage, ignoring armour and Toughness bonus.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"1d10*PR","penetration":"0","special":"Blast (PR), Flame, Warp Weapon"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"o4KS3UyWYvSa8Stl"}
{"name":"Psychic Communion","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Establishing a psychic link with his allies, the psyker ensures that they act in concert, the better to deliver righteous judgement on the Emperor&rsquo;s foes.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Increase Initiative  for self and allies","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Perception 35","action":"Full","focusPower":{"difficulty":10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"10*PR","sustained":"Free Action","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker selects a number of allies up to psy rating within range. While the power persists, the psyker and his affected allies add +2 to their Initiative. This can change an already established Initiative order.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"oKRplMSa4nSdzFiD"}
{"name":"Word of Beasts","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Many untrained psykers, both in the wilds of feral worlds and the depths of hive cities, develop an instinctive ability to communicate with beasts and lower creatures. Whether this ability represents true telepathy or something else is impossible to say.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"\"communicate\" with animals","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Fellowship 35","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"10","sustained":"No","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker opens a limited telepathic link with an animal, which resists the power with a Challenging (+0) Willpower test. If the psyker succeeds, he chooses one of the following efects: <br />Impression Reading: The psyker receives a mental impression of the animal&rsquo;s recent experiences. These are not thoughts in the sense of a sentient being, but merely vague impressions and unclear images. The GM determines the level of detail and form of the information received based on the intelligence and senses of the animal, as well as the PR of the psyker. The amount of information is based on the psyker&rsquo;s degrees of success on the Focus Power test.</p>\n<p>Empathic Link: The psyker establishes a bond with the animal that persists after the telepathic link ends. The animal follows the psyker and obeys his commands to the best of its ability, exactly as if he had tamed and trained it with the Wrangling special use of the Survival skill (see page 116 of the DARK HERESY Core Rulebook).</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"oL5bIQDmWYQEbHMc"}
{"name":"Iron Arm","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>The psyker&rsquo;s flesh transforms, hardening into a slick, living metal, weighing him down but also rendering him incredibly resistant. His new form allows him to shrug off small arms fire and crush his enemies with his bare hands.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Turn skin into living steel","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Strength 35, Toughness 35","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":-20,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"Self","sustained":"Free Action","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>While this power is in effect, the psyker gains the Unnatural Toughness and Unnatural Strength traits with ratings equal to half his psy rating, rounded up. However, his flesh&rsquo;s sturdier form weighs the psyker down, causing him to suffer a &ndash;10 penalty to his Agility characteristic while the power is in effect.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/Iron%20Arm.png","effects":[],"_id":"qpfR6DhqRwIRFDTi"}
{"name":"Spontaneous Combustion","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>In one of the purest displays of his power, the psyker ignites his enemies, burning them alive. The target&rsquo;s blood boils and flesh smoulders, and as the psyker&rsquo;s rage reaches its pinnacle, the target&rsquo;s body begins to explode in blasts of ash and flame.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Cause target to  catch fire","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Willpower 40","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"20*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Attack","effect":"","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"1d10+2+2*PR","penetration":"0","special":"Flame"}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/SpontaneousCombustion.png","effects":[],"_id":"rRayYxJRQvPaYyBi"}
{"name":"Perfect Timing","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>So accurate are the diviner&rsquo;s premonitions, that he can predict the exact moment his foe will expose himself as a target. Further, the psyker can forge a link with his allies, momentarily intertwining their fortunes, so that they might fire in perfect unison, already squeezing their weapons&rsquo; triggers before the foe is aware.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Allow self and allies to ignore cover whenshooting","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Perception 55","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Psyniscience"},"range":"3*PR","sustained":"Half Action","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>For the duration of this power, the psyker and a number of allies equal to his psy rating within range, ignore the effects of cover when firing on a target. If their attacks would strike a Hit Location on the enemy that would benefit from cover, that benefit is ignored. Allies affected by this power lose its benefits as soon as they move out of range.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/Perfect%20Timing.png","effects":[],"_id":"ttaefNq3kfmqFLxB"}
{"name":"Endurance","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Focussing his mind on the injured bodies of his allies, the psyker energises their biology, initiating rapid cell growth. In moments, shattered bones re-knit, gaping wounds close and heal, and the effects of combat damage disappear.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Heal multiple targetsâ€™ wounds","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Toughness 30","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"3*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>A number of allies in range equal to the psyker&rsquo;s psy rating, plus the psyker himself, recover wounds equal to half the psyker&rsquo;s psy rating, rounded up. They can also immediately overcome the effects of Pinning. This power is incredibly taxing and requires at least 12 hours of recovery before it may be used again.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/Endurance.png","effects":[],"_id":"vYv8JXLRSM8EMCgY"}
{"name":"Exorcism","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Many psykers who follow the path of Daemonology know that the best weapons against the Daemon are faith and psychic powers; only with the energies of the Warp is it truly possible to fight the Warp. Bolstering his ritual with psychic current, the psyker prepares to exorcise a Daemon.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Inflict damage on Daemon","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Willpower 40","action":"Full","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"5*PR","sustained":"Half Action","subtype":"Attack, Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker selects a single target character with the Daemonic trait, which opposes the power with a Willpower test. If the psyker wins the opposed test, the character suffers Willpower damage equal to the user&rsquo;s psy rating for each degree of success on the psyker&rsquo;s test.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"yFu1y9pGtQpT6SnN"}
{"name":"Assail","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>The psyker reaches out with his mind to pluck up whatever objects are available and hurl them at his target. If there is nothing suitable nearby, the psyker can direct his mental energies directly at his foe, pounding him with bolts of invisible force.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Smash target at range with invisible force","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Willpower 40","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"20*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Attack, Concentration","effect":"<p>If the psyker scores at least three degrees of success on the Focus Power test for this attack, the target is also thrown 1d5 metres away and knocked Prone. Certain especially large targets such as battle tanks, Greater Daemons, and Titans are immune to this effect at the Game Master&rsquo;s discretion.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"impact","formula":"1d10+PR","penetration":"2","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/Assil.png","effects":[],"_id":"QGJcUoSj24wRmddH"}
{"name":"Crush","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Rather than using his abilities to turn inanimate objects into weapons, the telekine focuses directly on his enemy to squeeze him in an invisible fist of power. Unless the target can repel the psychokinetic assault, he is bludgeoned horridly. Even should he survive, the overwhelming psychic force nonetheless pins him in place under a tremendous weight.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Squeeze target with invisible force","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Willpower 45","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":0,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"10*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Attack, Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker nominates a single target in range and line of sight who opposes this power with a Toughness test. If the target fails to resist the power, it suffers the attack below.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"impact","formula":"1d10+PR","penetration":"2","special":"Snare (PR/2)"}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/Crush.png","effects":[],"_id":"Ri3O5U1e0FVqnYzR"}
{"name":"Gate of Infinity","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Though it offers no physical attack, this power is nonetheless one of the most dangerous uses of the Telekinesis discipline. With it, the psyker tears open a hole in space so that he might pass through the Warp. Others might refuse to pass through the unreal pathway, however, fearful of any proximity to the Immaterium and its terrible denizens.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Open a portal  linking two distant  locations","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Psy rating 5","action":"Extended Action (3)","focusPower":{"difficulty":-20,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"1km*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker chooses a point anywhere within 5 metres times his psy rating, and opens a gate to the Immaterium at that point. He then chooses a point within range of the power, and opens an exit to the gate at that location. The psyker must be aware of the location in which he is opening the exit to the gate, either having visited it before, seen it from afar, or simply studied it on a map. The gate lasts for a number of rounds equal to the psyker&rsquo;s psy rating, and has a radius in metres equal to the psyker&rsquo;s psy rating as well. For the duration of the power, the two sides of the gate are linked, and any person or objects may pass between them freely provided they can fit through the gate. This power is incredibly taxing and requires at least 12 hours of recovery before it may be used again.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/GateofInfinity.png","effects":[],"_id":"YLdSuvXsGW193Egp"}
{"name":"Objuration Mechanicum","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>With this power, the psyker reaches into and disrupts the inner workings of nearby machines, jamming gears, blowing fuses, and severing power couplings. Those who rely on technology find themselves bereft of their support and helpless.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Intelligence 40","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":0,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"10*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker chooses a point anywhere within range and line of sight. This power creates a Haywire Field (see page 147) centred at this point, with a radius in metres equal to the psyker&rsquo;s psy rating.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/ObjurationMechanicum.png","effects":[],"_id":"xVU80tiEvRVkL20s"}
{"name":"Shockwave","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>The psyker uses his unnatural control of the physical world to amplify a sound to impossible levels. From clapping his hands together, stamping on a hab floor, or even shouting, the psyker creates a sound that transforms into a powerful shockwave, bursting eardrums and knocking people off their feet.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Release a concussive blast of energy","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Willpower 50","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":0,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"Self","sustained":"No","subtype":"Attack, Concentration","effect":"<p>Each character in the area of effect (other than the psyker) suffers the damage below. He is also pushed directly away from the psyker a number of metres equal to the psyker&rsquo;s psy rating.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"explosive","formula":"1d10+PR","penetration":"0","special":"Blast (PR)"}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/Shockwave.png","effects":[],"_id":"hQYvLBrNmZIJZjwA"}
{"name":"Telekine Dome","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>The psyker shields himself and nearby allies with a dome of mental force, large enough to surround his group and protect them from harm. The protective shield deflects bullets and lasblasts, sending them ricocheting in all directions.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Create a dome of invisible energy","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Psy rating 4","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":0,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"5*PR","sustained":"Free Action","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker chooses a point in range and line of sight, and creates a dome of invisible energy centred on that point with a radius equal to half the psyker&rsquo;s psy rating, rounded up. Each ally (including the psyker, potentially) standing inside the dome gains a number of Armour points equal to the psy rating to all Hit Locations against any attack that originated outside of the dome&rsquo;s radius. However, characters may still physically pass through the dome at no penalty.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/TelekineDome.png","effects":[],"_id":"VfQ2deo8kcwYBVKa"}
{"name":"Telekine Shield","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Using the energy of the Warp, the psyker erects a wall of tangible force that moves with him. The shimmering barrier stops bullets and deflects blades, but as more and more kinetic energy is directed at him, the psyker&rsquo;s mental shield wears down.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Create wall of invisible energy","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Intelligence 40","action":"half","focusPower":{"difficulty":20,"test":"Willlpower"},"range":"Self","sustained":"Free Action","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>For the duration of the power, all of the psyker&rsquo;s Hit Locations count as being protected by cover with an Armour Value equal to half this power&rsquo;s psy rating. This shield can be damaged just like normal cover by damage that exceeds the shield&rsquo;s Armour Value (see page 229). If the shield is reduced to 0 Armour points, the power stops, and is no longer sustained.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/TelekineShield.png","effects":[],"_id":"sNGLVbxRHXgVQlVb"}
{"name":"Telekinetic Control","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>The telekine calls on his powers to reach out farther than his flesh can extend, distorting reality to grasp objects with eldritch hands. With invisible fingers perhaps only betrayed with frosted rime or whispered breezes, few can notice his subtle manipulations.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Move and manipulate  objects at range","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Willpower 35","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":20,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"10*PR","sustained":"Half Action","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker chooses an object in range and line of sight with a weight no greater than 2 x PR kilograms. At the beginning of each of his turns, he can move the object in any direction up to a number of metres equal to twice his psy rating. If the object ever leaves the range of the power, the power ends.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/TelekineticControl.png","effects":[],"_id":"tJ1F49NTaTMVxxaV"}
{"name":"Vortex Explosion","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>In perhaps the ultimate display of his mastery of both the physical world and the Warp, the psyker tears open a hole twixt the two. Around the roiling vortex, the laws of physical space are undone as the ravenous predations of Chaos devour all in the vicinity. This power is extraordinarily dangerous, and not only to the psyker&rsquo;s enemies. The Vortex of Doom feeds on itself and can sustain its power without need of the psyker.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Summon a swirling torrent of Warp energy","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Psy rating 5","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"5*PR","sustained":"Half Action","subtype":"Attack, Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker chooses a point in range and line of sight, and creates a vortex of energy centred on that point that starts with a radius of 2 metres. Each character who is touching the vortex at the end of the psyker&rsquo;s turn suffers damage as detailed below.</p>\n<p>The psyker cannot voluntarily stop sustaining this power.</p>\n<p>Instead, at the beginning of each turn the psyker is sustaining the vortex, he must make a Challenging (+0) Willpower test with a &ndash;5 penalty for each metre in the vortex&rsquo;s current radius. If he passes the test, he may perform one of the following actions:</p>\n<p>&bull; Increase the vortex&rsquo;s radius by one metre.</p>\n<p>&bull; Decrease the vortex&rsquo;s radius by one metre.</p>\n<p>&bull; Move the vortex any direction a number of metres equal to the psyker&rsquo;s psy rating.</p>\n<p>If the psyker fails the Willpower test to sustain the vortex, or if he is unable to make the test due to other circumstances, its radius increases by one metre and it moves a number of metres equal to the psyker&rsquo;s psy rating in a random direction (see the Scatter Diagram on page 230). If the vortex&rsquo;s radius ever decreases to zero metres, the power ends and the vortex disappears. If the vortex&rsquo;s radius ever grows larger than the psyker&rsquo;s psy rating, it explodes, ending the power, and destroying the vortex. The psyker is hit by this damage regardless of his proximity to the exploding vortex as the energy of the Warp he was channelling lashes back into him.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"explosive","formula":"2d10+4*PR","penetration":"","special":"Blast (2*PR), pen=current vortex radius"}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/VortexofDoom.png","effects":[],"_id":"fEHWXejjkXbaHCjo"}
{"name":"Vortex of Doom","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>In perhaps the ultimate display of his mastery of both the physical world and the Warp, the psyker tears open a hole twixt the two. Around the roiling vortex, the laws of physical space are undone as the ravenous predations of Chaos devour all in the vicinity. This power is extraordinarily dangerous, and not only to the psyker&rsquo;s enemies. The Vortex of Doom feeds on itself and can sustain its power without need of the psyker.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Summon a swirling torrent of Warp energy","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Psy rating 5","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"5*PR","sustained":"Half Action","subtype":"Attack, Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker chooses a point in range and line of sight, and creates a vortex of energy centred on that point that starts with a radius of 2 metres. Each character who is touching the vortex at the end of the psyker&rsquo;s turn suffers damage as detailed below.</p>\n<p>The psyker cannot voluntarily stop sustaining this power.</p>\n<p>Instead, at the beginning of each turn the psyker is sustaining the vortex, he must make a Challenging (+0) Willpower test with a &ndash;5 penalty for each metre in the vortex&rsquo;s current radius. If he passes the test, he may perform one of the following actions:</p>\n<p>&bull; Increase the vortex&rsquo;s radius by one metre.</p>\n<p>&bull; Decrease the vortex&rsquo;s radius by one metre.</p>\n<p>&bull; Move the vortex any direction a number of metres equal to the psyker&rsquo;s psy rating.</p>\n<p>If the psyker fails the Willpower test to sustain the vortex, or if he is unable to make the test due to other circumstances, its radius increases by one metre and it moves a number of metres equal to the psyker&rsquo;s psy rating in a random direction (see the Scatter Diagram on page 230). If the vortex&rsquo;s radius ever decreases to zero metres, the power ends and the vortex disappears. If the vortex&rsquo;s radius ever grows larger than the psyker&rsquo;s psy rating, it explodes, ending the power, and destroying the vortex. The psyker is hit by this damage regardless of his proximity to the exploding vortex as the energy of the Warp he was channelling lashes back into him.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"explosive","formula":"2d10+2*PR","penetration":"","special":"Blast (2), pen=current vortex radius"}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/VortexofDoom.png","effects":[],"_id":"DkmzIt0UU0wo8IZs"}
{"name":"Dominate","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Demonstrating the superiority of his mutant mind, the telepath subverts his foe&rsquo;s will and forces him to act against his every inclination. Few psychic abilities are so rightly feared.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Force target to follow a single command","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Willpower 40","action":"Full","focusPower":{"difficulty":0,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"5*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker nominates a number targets in range and line of sight up to half his psy rating (rounded up) who oppose this power with a Willpower test. Each target that fails to resist the power must follow a simple command given by the psyker. Some example orders include &ldquo;Flee,&rdquo; &ldquo;Fall,&rdquo; or &ldquo;Attack your friend.&rdquo; If the command is a potentially suicidal act, each target receives a +20 to its Willpower test to Oppose the power. In all cases, the command must be achievable in a single round.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/Dominate.png","effects":[],"_id":"IO8AFkE2cOOiTdkR"}
{"name":"Erasure","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>With a surgeon&rsquo;s skill, the psyker opens up his target&rsquo;s mind and slices away a memory, removing it forever. This power is of immense utility to an Inquisitor&rsquo;s work, particularly one who wishes to operate discreetly, without the usual mess of an execution.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Remove a memory from targetâ€™s mind","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Fellowship 40","action":"Full","focusPower":{"difficulty":0,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"5*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker chooses a single foe in range and line of sight who opposes this power with a Willpower test. If he fails, the psyker removes a memory of a recent event from the target&rsquo;s mind. The psyker can only remove an amount of time from the target&rsquo;s memory up to 10 x PR minutes, and the event removed cannot have occurred more than PR hours prior to the use of this power. The enemy is left with a gap in his memory, with no recollection of what occurred during that time.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/Erasure.png","effects":[],"_id":"qsPHuIv9yZiTZza9"}
{"name":"Hallucination","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>The human mind&rsquo;s grasp on reality is fragile and easily manipulated with sufficient power. With his own psychic senses, the telepath touches the psyche of his target and severs its connection to normal existence.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Cause target to suffer uncontrolled visions","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Fellowship 40","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":0,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"10*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker nominates a single target in range and line of sight who opposes this power with a Willpower test. If the target fails to resist the power, it must roll on Table 5&ndash;3: Hallucinogenic Effects on page 146, and immediately apply the effects. The effect rolled on the table lasts for a number of rounds equal to half the psyker&rsquo;s psy rating, rounded up.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/Hallucination.png","effects":[],"_id":"EQJuDXuGI2E0jMix"}
{"name":"Invisibility","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Clouding enemy minds, the psyker obscures his allies from their foes&rsquo; senses. Though eyes and other senses detect them as normal, their minds do not perceive them, save for a slight distortion in their vision.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Obscure targets  from view","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Agility 30, psy rating 4","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"10*PR","sustained":"Free Action","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker nominates a single target within range and line of sight (this can be the psyker himself). For the duration of the power, the target counts having the Stealth skill at Known (rank 1), and gains a bonus to Stealth tests equal to +5 times the psyker&rsquo;s psy rating. Additionally, all ranged attacks made against the target suffer a penalty equal to &ndash;5 times the psyker&rsquo;s psy rating. If the target moves beyond the power&rsquo;s range, he loses this power&rsquo;s benefits.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/Invisibility.png","effects":[],"_id":"2gEU4plo3e1pJo6P"}
{"name":"Mental Fortitude","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Drawing from the limitless potential of the Warp, the psyker augments the mental abilities of his targets, providing defence against the stresses of combat and the terrors of the galaxy.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Share Adamantium Faith talent with allies","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Adamantium Faith","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"3*PR","sustained":"Free Action","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>For the duration of this power, a number of allies up to the psyker&rsquo;s psy rating within range count as having the Adamantium Faith talent. Allies affected by this power lose its benefits as soon as they move out of range.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/MentalFortitude.png","effects":[],"_id":"bp8Jy9ouW7lzGds5"}
{"name":"Psychic Shriek","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Drawing a deep soul-breath, the psyker unleashes a rippling Warp tide that sears the souls and blasts the minds of those in its path. The violent psychic wave is enough to overwhelm and shut down the minds of those it strikes, while those not slain outright are left reeling and dazed.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Attack target with a psychic wave","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Psy rating 3","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":0,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"10*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Attack","effect":"","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"explosive","formula":"1d10+2+2*PR","penetration":"","special":"concussive (1)"}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/PsychicShriek.png","effects":[],"_id":"J2CkXFOWSdQ2H1bk"}
{"name":"Puppet Master","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>In the ultimate expression of telepathic power, the psyker utterly crushes his target&rsquo;s will, locking him away in a dark corner of his own mind and taking complete control of his body. After recovering their wits, those subjected to this power are often struck with bouts of insecurity, never certain again if their actions are truly their own.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Control the actions of target","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Fellowship 55","action":"Full","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"10*PR","sustained":"Special","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker nominates a single target in range and line of sight with total wounds no greater than 3 times the psyker&rsquo;s psy rating, who opposes this power with a Willpower test. If the target fails to resist the power, it is controlled by the psyker like a puppet. For the duration of the power, the psyker can divide his Actions between himself and the target. The dominated target uses its own Characteristics, but at &ndash;10 due to the crudity of the control. If at any point the psyker would make the target perform a potentially suicidal action, the target can attempt a Challenging (+0) Opposed Willpower test to try to break free of the power. Additionally, the power breaks as soon as the target moves out of range.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/PuppetMaster.png","effects":[],"_id":"76Wp4ljGnCFGcw0Q"}
{"name":"Telepathic Link","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>In this, the simplest yet purest expression of his powers, the telepath establishes a mental connection to another, linking their minds and allowing him to receive or transmit thoughts. When stealth is essential, such silent communication is ideal.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Create a mental connection with target","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Willpower 35","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"20*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>The psyker chooses a person in range and line of sight who opposes this power with a Willpower test. If the target fails, the psyker can either read the person&rsquo;s thoughts or send him a brief mental message.</p>\n<p>&bull; Thought Reading: The psyker reads the target&rsquo;s thoughts, with the GM determining the nature of the information gained. The more degrees of success scored on the Focus Power test, the more information is gained overall. The higher the PR of the power, the more secretive the information gained.</p>\n<p>&bull; Thought Sending: The psyker causes a message to appear in the target&rsquo;s mind as if he has just heard it spoken aloud. The message can be no longer than 5 x PR seconds long. If the target of this power is aware of what the psyker is trying to do, he can voluntarily fail the opposed Willpower test, counting as having rolled a 100.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/TelepathicLink.png","effects":[],"_id":"t9mTZ4R5MdCyXm5D"}
{"name":"Terrify","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"psychicPower","data":{"description":"<p>Turning an eldritch key, the psyker unlocks his target&rsquo;s deepest and strongest fears, exposing him to the worst recesses of his own psyche. These nightmarish visions are enough to drive even the strongest helplessly mad.</p>","source":"","shortDescription":"Inflict nightmarish visions on target","cost":0,"prerequisite":"Fellowship 45","action":"Half","focusPower":{"difficulty":-10,"test":"Willpower"},"range":"10*PR","sustained":"No","subtype":"Concentration","effect":"<p>Slithering deep into the mind of his victim, the psyker unearths their greatest failings, greatest weaknesses, and greatest fears. Using these as tools against his opponent, the psyker can turn even the most courageous warriors into pathetic, whimpering cowards before him. The psyker nominates a single target in range and line of sight who opposes this power with a Willpower test.</p>\n<p>If the target fails to resist the power, it must roll on Table 8&ndash;11: Shock on page 287, adding +10 times the psyker&rsquo;s psy rating to the roll in place of the normal addition for degrees of failure, and immediately apply the effects.</p>","damage":{"zone":"bolt","type":"energy","formula":"","penetration":"","special":""}},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_resources/icons/Terrify.png","effects":[],"_id":"q9RfWR2cswaZutWZ"}
